SIMPLE: taenia
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Taenia
<hw>Tae"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Taeniae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a ribbon, a
tapeworm.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of
intestinal worms which includes the common tapeworms of man. See
<er>Tapeworm</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A band; a structural line; --
applied to several bands and lines of nervous matter in the
brain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The fillet, or band, at the
bottom of a Doric frieze, separating it from the architrave.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Teniacide</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Taeniacide</ent>⟦br⟧
